Buenos Aires Mayor Macri Expected to Win Runoff Vote, La Nacion Poll Shows

-- B y   R i c h a r d   J a r v i e
-- 
2011-07-24T13:31:28Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-24/macri-expected-to-win-buenos-aires-runoff-nacion-poll-shows.html
Buenos Aires  Mayor Mauricio Macri
will be re-elected in a July 31 runoff against Senator Daniel Filmus, according to a poll published in La Nacion newspaper.  Macri, a former president of Club Atletico Boca Juniors
soccer club and son of a wealthy businessman, drew 52.1 percent
support, while Filmus, a former education minister who’s a
member of President Cristina Fernandez de Kirchner’s Victory
Front alliance, had 32.8 percent.  The poll of 916 people by Buenos Aires-based Poliarquia
Consultores, taken July 16-22, has a margin of error of 3.3
percentage points.  In the first round of voting on July 10, Macri took 47.1
percent of votes and Filmus 27.8 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Richard Jarvie in Buenos Aires at 
 rjarvie@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Joshua Goodman  at 
 jgoodman19@bloomberg.net . 